BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12
13
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 376 of Title 59, unless there is
14
15
created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. As used in this section, “direct-to-consumer pharmaceutical
16
17
advertising” means any promotional communication targeting consumers
17
18
including, but not limited to, television, radio, print media,
18
19
digital platforms, and social media, that markets prescription
19
20
drugs.
20
21
B. No person or entity may engage in direct-to-consumer
21
22
pharmaceutical advertising within this state.
22
23
C. The State Board of Pharmacy may assess an administrative
23
24
penalty against a person or entity who violates this section or
24
Req. No. 2379 Page 1

1
fails to comply with a rule adopted under this section, not to
1
2
exceed Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00) per day for each violation.
2
3
Each day a violation continues may be considered a separate
3
4
violation.
4
5
D. The Board may adopt rules as necessary to implement this
5
6
section.
6
7
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
